# SubTrak Error Log

This file is a living document. Every time a runtime, build, or type error is encountered and fixed, append an entry below using the format shown. The agent MUST read this file before making any changes to avoid repeating known mistakes.

---

## Error: Amplify SSR Hydration Mismatch
- Symptom: `Text content does not match server-rendered HTML` when using Amplify auth state in components
- Root cause: Amplify auth state is client-only; server render produces different HTML than client hydration
- Fix: All components using `getCurrentUser()`, `Hub.listen()`, or any Amplify auth API must have `'use client'` directive. Initialize Amplify in a dedicated client component (`AmplifyConfig.tsx`) that renders `null`.
- Prevention: Never call Amplify auth functions in server components. Always add `'use client'` to any file importing from `aws-amplify/auth` or `aws-amplify/utils`.

## Error: Prisma Client Multiple Instances in Dev
- Symptom: `warn(prisma-client) Already 10 Prisma Clients actively running` in dev mode
- Root cause: Next.js hot reload creates new Prisma client instances on every file change
- Fix: Use singleton pattern in `lib/prisma.ts`:
  ```typescript
  const globalForPrisma = globalThis as unknown as { prisma: PrismaClient };
  export const prisma = globalForPrisma.prisma || new PrismaClient();
  if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') globalForPrisma.prisma = prisma;
  ```
- Prevention: Never instantiate `new PrismaClient()` outside `lib/prisma.ts`. Always import from `@/lib/prisma`.

## Error: Gemini Invalid JSON Response
- Symptom: `SyntaxError: Unexpected token` when parsing Gemini output
- Root cause: Gemini sometimes wraps JSON in markdown code fences or adds commentary
- Fix: Strip markdown fences before parsing: `response.replace(/```json\n?/g, '').replace(/```\n?/g, '').trim()`. Then `JSON.parse()` inside try/catch. Validate with Zod after parsing.
- Prevention: Always instruct Gemini to return raw JSON only (no markdown, no commentary). Always wrap parse in try/catch with fallback error message.

## Error: Tailwind v4 CSS Variable Conflicts with shadcn
- Symptom: shadcn components appear unstyled or with wrong colors after init
- Root cause: Tailwind v4 uses `@theme inline` block and CSS custom properties that can conflict with shadcn's default CSS variable names
- Fix: After `shadcn init`, verify that `globals.css` merges both the project's existing custom properties and shadcn's required variables.
- Prevention: After any shadcn init or component add, check `globals.css` for conflicts.

## Error: Prisma preinstall script fails on Windows with npm 10.x
- Symptom: `ERR_INVALID_ARG_TYPE: The "file" argument must be of type string. Received undefined` during `npm install`
- Root cause: Prisma's `preinstall` script spawns a child process that fails under npm 10.9.x on Windows due to an undefined binary path
- Fix: Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --ignore-scripts` then `npx prisma generate` manually after install completes
- Prevention: Always use `--ignore-scripts` when installing on this project. Run `npx prisma generate` as a separate step after install.

## Error: Next.js 16 middleware deprecation warning
- Symptom: Build warning `The "middleware" file convention is deprecated. Please use "proxy" instead.`
- Root cause: Next.js 16 renamed the `middleware.ts` convention to `proxy.ts`
- Fix: The middleware still works in v16 but shows a deprecation warning. When ready, rename `middleware.ts` to `proxy.ts` and update the export to use the new API.
- Prevention: For Next.js 16+ projects, use the `proxy.ts` convention instead of `middleware.ts`.

## Error: Prisma v6 generated client has no index.ts
- Symptom: `Cannot find module '@/lib/generated/prisma'` when importing PrismaClient
- Root cause: Prisma v6 `prisma-client` generator outputs `client.ts` and `enums.ts` but no `index.ts` barrel file, so directory imports fail
- Fix: Create `lib/generated/prisma/index.ts` that re-exports from `./client` and `./enums`. This file will be overwritten on `prisma generate`, so re-create it manually after each generate.
- Prevention: After every `npx prisma generate`, verify that `lib/generated/prisma/index.ts` exists.

## Error: Hydration mismatch from auth-dependent rendering
- Symptom: React warning "A tree hydrated but some attributes of the server rendered HTML didn't match the client properties"
- Root cause: Navbar and Footer rendered different HTML on server (user=null) vs client (user=authenticated), causing SSR/CSR mismatch
- Fix: Add a `mounted` state initialized to `false`, set to `true` in `useEffect`. Gate all auth-dependent rendering on `mounted && user` instead of just `user`. Render a placeholder before mount.
- Prevention: Any client component that conditionally renders based on auth state MUST use a `mounted` guard to prevent hydration mismatches.

## Error: Nested button inside button in StatementUploader
- Symptom: Console error `<button> cannot contain a nested <button>`
- Root cause: The upload drop zone was a `<button>` element containing a child `<button>` for clearing the file
- Fix: Changed the outer `<button>` to a `<div role="button" tabIndex={0}>` with keyboard handler
- Prevention: Never nest interactive HTML elements (`<button>`, `<a>`) inside other interactive elements. Use `<div role="button">` for container-level click targets.

## Error: Failed to sync user to database after Cognito confirmation
- Symptom: Console error "Failed to sync user to database" after signup confirmation
- Root cause: The login page used dynamic `import("aws-amplify/auth")` which is fragile and can fail silently
- Fix: Import `getCurrentUser` statically. Created shared `lib/sync-user.ts` with `syncCurrentUserToDb()`.
- Prevention: Never use dynamic `import()` for auth modules. Always use static imports for `aws-amplify/auth` functions.

## Error: Unauthorized on API calls after database recreation
- Symptom: `401 Unauthorized` on upload/subscription API calls even though user is logged in
- Root cause: User sync to DB only happened during signup confirmation. After DB recreation, user record is missing while Cognito session is still valid.
- Fix: Created `lib/sync-user.ts` with `syncCurrentUserToDb()` that uses `getCurrentUser()` + `fetchUserAttributes()` to upsert the user record. Called on login, signup confirmation, and on page load for all auth-protected pages.
- Prevention: Always call `syncCurrentUserToDb()` on any auth-protected page's initial load. This ensures the user record exists even if the DB was reset.

## Error: pdf-parse v2 "fake worker" / "cannot find module" in Node.js
- Symptom: `pdfParse is not a function` then `Error setting up fake worker: Cannot find module`
- Root cause: `pdf-parse` v2.4.x tries to set up a web worker, which fails in Node.js API routes
- Fix: Removed all server-side PDF text extraction. Instead, send the raw PDF file directly to Gemini as base64 `inlineData`. Gemini natively reads PDFs via its multimodal API.
- Prevention: For PDF processing, prefer sending files directly to Gemini's multimodal API rather than extracting text server-side. Avoids all Node.js/worker compatibility issues.

## Error: Gemini API quota exceeded on gemini-2.0-flash
- Symptom: `429 RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED: Quota exceeded` when calling Gemini API
- Root cause: Free-tier quota limits on `gemini-2.0-flash` model were hit
- Fix: Switched to `gemini-3-flash-preview` which has separate quota limits
- Prevention: Monitor API usage. Keep model name in `lib/ai.ts` as a single source of truth so it can be changed easily. Consider adding retry logic with exponential backoff for rate limits.

## Error: Account page edit/preferences not functional
- Symptom: "Edit" button on account settings does nothing. Preference toggles are static HTML with no click handlers.
- Root cause: Account page was a static mockup — no state management, no API calls, no form handling
- Fix: Rewrote account page with editable profile fields (React Hook Form + Zod), functional toggle switches with state, API routes for GET/PUT user profile, and `syncCurrentUserToDb()` on load.
- Prevention: Never ship static mockup UI for interactive features. Always wire up state management and API calls when building forms and toggles.

## Security Fix: Authentication Forgeable via Client-Sent Header (CRITICAL)
- Symptom: API routes trusted `x-user-cognito-id` header for authentication, allowing impersonation
- Root cause: No server-side JWT verification. Any attacker could set this header to any Cognito ID.
- Fix: Installed `aws-jwt-verify`. Rewrote `lib/auth.ts` to use `CognitoJwtVerifier` which verifies Cognito ID tokens against the JWKS endpoint. Created `lib/client-auth.ts` with `getIdToken()`, `authHeaders()`, and `authHeadersFormData()` helpers to send Bearer tokens from client. Updated ALL API calls and hooks to use JWT tokens instead of raw cognitoId headers.
- Prevention: Never trust client-supplied identity headers. Always verify JWTs server-side. Use `requireAuth(request)` from `lib/auth.ts` in every API route.

## Security Fix: /api/users POST Unauthenticated (CRITICAL)
- Symptom: Anyone could POST to `/api/users` to create/update user records for any cognitoId
- Root cause: The endpoint had zero authentication — it accepted any cognitoId in the body
- Fix: Added JWT verification via `getVerifiedCognitoId(request)`. Validates that the JWT `sub` matches the submitted cognitoId. Added Zod input validation.
- Prevention: Every API route that writes data must call `requireAuth()` or `getVerifiedCognitoId()`. Never accept unverified identity in request body.

## Security Fix: cognitoId Leaked in Profile API Response (LOW)
- Symptom: `GET /api/users/profile` returned `cognitoId` field to the client
- Root cause: The response included all user fields without filtering
- Fix: Removed `cognitoId` from the JSON response in both GET and PUT handlers
- Prevention: Never return internal identifiers (cognitoId, AWS IDs) in API responses. Only return fields the client needs.

## Security Fix: Unsafe Type Casts in Subscriptions API (MEDIUM)
- Symptom: Query parameters for `status` and `billingCycle` used `as` casts without validation
- Root cause: `searchParams.get()` returns raw strings that were cast to Prisma enum types without checking
- Fix: Added Zod `querySchema` with `z.enum()` validation for `status`, `billingCycle`, and `z.string().max(200)` for `search`. Only validated values reach the Prisma query.
- Prevention: Always validate query parameters with Zod before passing to database queries. Never use `as` casts on user input.

## Security Fix: No Rate Limiting on Gemini Extraction (HIGH)
- Symptom: A user could call `POST /api/extract/:id` unlimited times, running up Gemini API costs
- Root cause: No rate limiting on the extraction endpoint
- Fix: Created `lib/rate-limit.ts` with in-memory rate limiter. Applied to extract POST: 5 requests per hour per user. Returns 429 with retry-after when exceeded.
- Prevention: All AI/external API endpoints must have rate limiting. Use `checkRateLimit()` from `lib/rate-limit.ts`.

## Security Fix: Redundant syncCurrentUserToDb Calls (MEDIUM)
- Symptom: `syncCurrentUserToDb()` called on every page load, making unnecessary API calls
- Root cause: Every auth-protected page independently called sync on mount
- Fix: Centralized sync to `UserProfileProvider` with a `hasSynced` ref that prevents re-syncing within the same session. Reset on sign-in/sign-out events.
- Prevention: Use the `UserProfileProvider` as the single source of truth for user sync. Never call `syncCurrentUserToDb()` from individual pages.

## Security Fix: console.error Leaking Sensitive Data (LOW)
- Symptom: Error details (stack traces, auth errors) logged to browser console in production
- Root cause: `console.error()` calls in catch blocks for sign-out and EmailJS errors
- Fix: Removed all `console.error()` calls from client-side code. Errors are shown to users via toast notifications only.
- Prevention: Never use `console.error()` in production client code. Use toast notifications for user-facing errors. For server-side, use structured logging.

